import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="group", y="group_size", data=data, ci=None, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.axhline(y=data['group_size'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Group Size: {:.2f}'.format(data['group_size'].mean()))
    ax.set(xlabel='Group', ylabel='Group Size')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.title('What is the average group size?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='group_size', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['group_size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['group_size'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['group_size'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['group_size'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    group_size = data['group_size'].value_counts()
    labels = group_size.index
    sizes = group_size.values
    plt.pie(sizes, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the most common group size?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
